Great news — on .NET 10 SDK, **you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property is only required for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs.

Instead, add a `"test"` section to your `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

This tells `dotnet test` to use MTP natively. Arguments are passed directly (no `--` separator needed).

Want me to update your `global.json` and remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from the `.csproj`?
